# Default config for running the CI workflow locally with `act`
# (https://github.com/nektos/act). The hosted GitHub Actions workflow is the
# source of truth; this lets you reproduce it on your machine.
#
# Use the catthehacker runner image (closest to GitHub's ubuntu-latest, ships
# node so JS actions like Swatinem/rust-cache work). On Apple Silicon, act runs
# the arm64 variant natively — fast, and avoids QEMU compiler crashes. Add
# `--container-architecture linux/amd64` on the command line if you need to
# reproduce an x86_64-specific issue (slower, emulated).
-P ubuntu-latest=catthehacker/ubuntu:act-latest

# Usage:
#   act push -j fmt
#   act push -j clippy
#   act push -j test --matrix os:ubuntu-latest
# (macos-latest / windows-latest matrix legs only run on real GitHub runners.)
